            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong> and your <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>spinach </strong>to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it until wilted</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water </strong>until it's cool enough to handle, then squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1580805935745-x200.jpg",
